  "bib_entries": {
    "12714392": {
      "title": "On the convergence of the block nonlinear Gauss-Seidel method under convex constraints",
      "abstract": "We give new convergence results for the block Gauss-Seidel method for problems where the feasible set is the Cartesian product of m closed convex sets, under the assumption that the sequence generated by the method has limit points. We show that the method is globally convergent for m=2 and that for m>2 convergence can be established both when the objective function f is componentwise strictly quasiconvex with respect to m-2 components and when f is pseudoconvex. Finally, we consider a proximal point modification of the method and we state convergence results without any convexity assumption on the objective function."
    }
